    // and 'y' can be transformed into 'z' (where z divides y), then 'x' can effectively be
    // transformed into 'z' through a chain of operations (x -> y -> z).
    // This implies that if 'd' is a divisor of any element in the array, we might be able to
    // transform some elements into 'd'.

